Key Match Events: Paul Stirling top-scored with 88 from 92 balls, leading Ireland to a total of 284 for nine.
Jason Smith struck a defiant 91 from 93 balls with nine fours and four sixes for South Africa.
South Africa began their run chase disastrously, plunging to 10 for three inside five overs.
Kyle Verreynne's counterattack yielded 38 from 36 balls.
Craig Young's outswinger found Tristan Stubbs' edge, ending his innings at 20 runs from 45 balls.
Andile Phehlukwayo briefly threatened a counter-attack with 23 from 28 balls.
Harry Tector scored a fine 60 from 48 deliveries.
Post-Match Reflections: South Africa had already clinched the series with comprehensive victories in the first two matches, but the loss in the third ODI will leave a sour taste after a disappointing tour.
